dreams.dream: I am working at home at my computer. The windows are open and my neighbours, who are usually noisy, can hear me. Their friend starts to speak to me from the window. The neighbour joins the conversation but his wife gives me a contemptuous look. She later on tidies my desk, but it makes it more messy. I decide to tidy it again and while plugging in a cable into my computer, the cable breaks and it makes weird electrical noises. I am afraid of getting electrocuted.
dreams.interpretation:
This dream could represent feelings of vulnerability and unease in your personal or professional life. Your work at home symbolizes a sense of productivity and personal focus. The open windows may suggest a desire for connection or being heard by others, specifically your noisy neighbors. 

The friend speaking to you through the window indicates unexpected social interactions or communication from unexpected sources. The neighbor joining the conversation could represent a desire for involvement or intrusion in your personal or professional affairs. The wife's contemptuous look suggests feelings of judgment or disapproval from someone close to you.

The tidying of your desk by the wife could symbolize attempts to control or manage your work environment, but it ultimately results in more chaos or disorganization. This may reflect feelings of frustration or ineffectiveness in handling your responsibilities or daily tasks.

The broken cable and electrical noises when plugging it in may represent a fear of potential disruptions or mishaps in your work or personal life. The fear of getting electrocuted suggests a fear of negative consequences or harm associated with your endeavors.

Overall, this dream could signify a need for better boundaries, effective communication, and a sense of control in your personal and professional relationships. It could also indicate a desire for recognition or validation from others, while also acknowledging and addressing any fears or anxieties that may be hindering your progress.
dreams.title: Chaos and Contempt: A Noisy Neighbour, Tidying Mishaps, and Electrocution Fears

The work event represents a setting where you desire recognition and validation for your contributions. The fact that you are being denied a gift meant for all attendees suggests that you feel unappreciated or overlooked in comparison to your colleagues.

The lack of support from your colleagues further emphasizes the sense of isolation and disconnection you may be experiencing. It could indicate a desire for more collaboration and teamwork in your professional life.

The difficulty you encounter in following the lunch area rule may represent challenges or obstacles you face in navigating workplace protocols or expectations. Feeling unable to meet these expectations could suggest a fear of failure or a sense of being overwhelmed by the complexities of your job.

Being told off by the staff may reflect a fear of authority figures or feeling reprimanded for not adhering to certain guidelines. It could imply a need to better understand and comply with the rules and structures in your workplace.

Overall, this dream suggests a longing for appreciation, support, and a desire to navigate the dynamics of your work environment effectively. It may be valuable to explore ways to improve communication and collaboration with your colleagues, as well as develop a better understanding of the expectations and rules within your professional setting.

dreams.dream:
i was rummaging around in a pile of stuff on the shelf by by front door and found a pouch of lalaloopsies i used to play with when i was little. including one that i had take down to the park in the snow, where i lost one of her lalaloopsy friends. a new reporter told me that they think someone had found my lost lalaloopsy in australia or spain or somewhere like that.
flash forward, me and my family and a random old woman who i don’t know but didn’t question are sat in a car, driving through a very orange, dry landscape. we heard about an epidemic that had begun in spain. the disease could be caught in the plants and shrubbery in the area (some sort of spore or pollen) and the native animals were also carriers. so basically we are in a foreign country during a pandemic and no one could help us. my family are panicking and looking for a solution when suddenly the car encounters a very inconvenient obstacle. an enormous gorilla had begun banging its fist of the windows and doors of our car. my family was screaming and yelling, fearing for their lives when suddenly, the gorilla caught hold of the latch that opened the boot, and before we knew it a gorilla had joined our party. if things couldn’t get any worse, the gorilla had been followed by a solitary coyote who leaped onto our boot. through the shouting and confusion we noticed that the animals were actually quite friendly and allowed us to pet them. but nonetheless, they were potential carriers of a deadly disease and they had to be evacuated. so i grabbed the coyote and threw it out of my car window, shortly followed by the gorilla, who was strikingly smaller and lighter that anticipated. we moved on and after hours of looking for solutions, my family came across a woman who was clearly knowledgeable about this area (some sort of guide) who told us we should be fine as long as we avoid the bushes and wildlife. do you know what the strange old woman did? she waddled into the bushes while no one was looking, as did my dog. i chased after my dog as i don’t want him to die and threw him up to my dad. my dad pulled me up but harshly threw me on the floor and scolded me for disobeying the guide. he apologised and said he was stressed out afterwards and i forgave him. as the family were approaching the car again, i spotted the old lady who had returned. i asked her if she was okay and she responded “i’m good thank you dearie, but i think a coyote bit me” as she revealed a nasty bite mark on her arm. i alerted my mum but subsequently woke up.
dreams.interpretation:
This dream could be interpreted in a few ways:

1. Nostalgia and Lost Connections: The first part of the dream, where you find a pouch of Lalaloopsies from your childhood, represents nostalgia and rediscovering lost connections. It may suggest that you are exploring your past and reminiscing about simpler times.

2. Fear and Uncertainty: The second part of the dream, where you encounter a pandemic in a foreign country, reflects a sense of fear and uncertainty. The epidemic and the inability to find help represent feelings of vulnerability and being overwhelmed by forces beyond your control.

3. Inner Strength and Adaptability: The gorilla and the coyote that join your party can symbolize the challenges and obstacles in your life. Despite the initial fear and chaos they cause, you discover that they are friendly and allow you to pet them. This may suggest that even in difficult situations, you have the ability to adapt and find a way to handle challenges.

4. Trust and Betrayal: The actions of the old woman and your dog are significant. The old woman going into the bushes despite being warned symbolizes a lack of trust or rational decision-making. Meanwhile, your dog following her implies loyalty and protection. Your dad scolding you for disobeying the guide, and subsequently apologizing, highlights the theme of trust and potential betrayal within familial relationships.

Overall, the dream may reflect your desire for connection, the need to navigate an uncertain situation, and the importance of trust and adaptability in overcoming challenges. It may also indicate unresolved emotions from the past and the need to address them in order to move forward.
dreams.title: Lost Lalaloopsies and Pandemic Perils: A Harrowing Journey with Unlikely Companions

dreams.dream:
When I was a kid, I often had the same dream about our flat's entrance door left open. Every time in my dream, once I had realised it, I became dreadfully scared of someone bad entering our home. I ran to the door and when I was trying to close it, something was wrong with the lock: one time it was simply broken, another time it was actually a door handle that came out of the door once I pulled it. And these dream often involved someone standing behind the door (I could see them in the peephole), so I had to try to lock the door without letting them know of my presence. In most cases I failed, and the person on the other side of the door pulled it, I became terrified, and the dream ended.
What is the meaning of this dream? Why it was reoccurring?
dreams.interpretation:
Dreams about open doors and the fear of someone bad entering your home often represent feelings of vulnerability, insecurity, and a lack of control in your waking life. As a child, you may have experienced situations or events that made you feel unsafe or exposed, which is why this dream reoccurred.

The open door symbolizes an opportunity for negative influences or harmful situations to enter your life. Your fear and urgency to close the door emphasize your desire to protect yourself and maintain a sense of security. The recurring theme of the broken lock or door handle suggests that you feel powerless and unable to effectively defend yourself against potential threats.

The person standing behind the door represents the unknown and the fear of the consequences that may arise if you fail to secure your boundaries. This individual symbolizes the potential harm that could come from allowing external influences into your personal space, which further amplifies your fear.

The inability to successfully lock the door and the subsequent terror you experience in the dream reflects your anxieties about the potential consequences of failing to protect yourself from negative external forces. This recurring dream may indicate a need for a stronger sense of security, control, and boundaries in your waking life.

It could be beneficial to reflect on any current or past situations where you feel vulnerable, exposed, or lacking control. By identifying and addressing these concerns, you can work towards creating a greater sense of security and empowerment in your waking life, which may help reduce the occurrence of this dream.
dreams.title: Incessant Fear: Breaking Locks, Hidden Faces

dreams.dream:
I was part of a vampire coven in my hometown.  We weren't big or powerful, but we were family, and we didn’t usually feed on human blood but used animal blood instead, mostly livestock.  There was me, another older woman called Annie, and a man called Tony who was our leader.  We all lived together in a cosy set of rooms hollowed out from caves under the town hall.  There was a hidden entrance to our caves in the old prisoner's cells in the basement of the town hall.
A few years after I became a vampire, we found a new vampire called Matt who had been experimenting with what his powers could do, but Tony asked him to slow down with trying things out when he came to live with our coven, to make sure he wouldn't get into any danger.  He complied but wasn't happy about it.
We went to a few town meetings about various unimportant things, and after a few months, we met another vampire called Anthony there.  He was very confident and we weren't sure how long he'd been a vampire or where he'd come from, but he was happy to join our coven and had a grasp of basic things he could do as a vampire.
When Anthony joined the coven, he started to suggest that we should be exercising our powers more to keep our human town in check, and he thought we should feed on the humans more, which would make us stronger.  His suggestions started subtle and got progressively more obvious, but Tony turned down only some of them, such as the ones that said humans were lesser than vampires.  Throughout this, Matt was increasingly more upset and anti-social, because Tony was listening to Anthony's ideas but had turned down Matt when he presented similar ideas.
I decided to talk to Tony about the problem since Matt refused to.  I described the problem from different angles and Tony realised what he'd been doing, and said he felt really bad about it.  He mentioned a prophecy detailing how vampires could take their place among humans in the open and suggested that Matt could be the one to fulfil the prophecy.  Tony went to fetch Matt so we could discuss it.
While he was gone, my mind wandered and I started to look around the room a bit, and I climbed the rough-hewn walls of the room, trying to get comfortable.  I found a spot about halfway up the wall and settled into a nook, sitting upside down.  Tony and Matt returned and looked up at me with shock, wondering how I'd gotten up there.  I explained that it was no hassle really, the walls were pretty easy to climb.  Tony pointed out that he had carefully sanded the walls down to be smooth.  I took a closer look and realised the walls were very smooth, but I had climbed them anyway.  Tony listed this, among some other vampiric stuff I'd only seen myself do, and realised that I must be the person in the prophecy, not Matt.  He asked me how I became a vampire.
I had a flashback to going deep-sea diving with someone else who I didn't know well.  I think we had become friends while on holiday.  There was a problem with my equipment and I was about to run out of air, but we were too far down to surface in time.  My diving partner said there was a way to stop me from dying, and asked if I trusted her.  I said yes, and she had bitten my neck before I could react, but I remember this instant feeling of happiness.  I woke up just after she bit me.
dreams.interpretation:
This dream appears to have a strong connection to the idea of power dynamics and the consequences of being influenced by others. Specifically, the dream suggests that the dreamer is aware of the different influences that can impact people, both positive and negative. The dreamer appears to belong to a group that has some sort of shared identity, as illustrated through the vampire coven. This group is presented as very familial and connected, which might reflect the dreamer's need to belong and find acceptance.

The introduction of new members and their differing beliefs illustrates how external influences can impact a group or individual. The conflict that arises between Matt and the other vampires highlights how easily affected people can be by others' ideas. The dreamer is the only one who steps in to try to solve the problem, which might show the dreamer's sense of responsibility to their group.

The dreamer's climbing of the walls could represent a desire for independence and the ability to choose one's own path. The walls being smooth, yet still climbable, could suggest that the dreamer is able to overcome obstacles and find a way forward despite the challenges. The fact that Tony, the leader, realizes that the dreamer is the chosen one in the prophecy indicates that the dreamer has unique abilities and individual strengths that set them apart from the rest of the group.

Lastly, the diving experience suggests that the dreamer has a sense of adventure and willingness to try new things, even at great risk. The feeling of happiness despite being bitten might also indicate a desire to find pleasure and fulfillment in life, even if it means taking a risk or stepping outside of one's comfort zone. Overall, the dream suggests that the dreamer is aware of power dynamics and the consequences of being influenced by others, but also has a strong sense of independence and an adventurous spirit.
dreams.title: Coven Chronicles: Unveiling Prophecies and Unintended Ascension
